The paper is about mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the analysis of submodular functions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper uses probabilistic techniques to analyze the performance of mechanisms, which is a common approach in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
